            "instructions": "Body paragraphs. One paragraph per line. The first line displays with the red accent.",
            "rows": 8,
            "default_value": "The Village Rate is fixed in accordance with the provisions of the Local Government Act 1985 (as amended). Rates are collected on behalf of Port St Mary Commissioners by The Treasury. Should you wish to pay your rates within the village,\nPort St Mary Commissioners prepares its financial statements in accordance with the Isle of Man Statement of Recommended Practice 2007 (SORP) and the requirements of the Audit Act 2006.\nThe SORP is recognised under the Audit Act 2006 and the Accounts and Audit Regulations 2007 as representing proper accounting practice.\nCopies of the audited financial statements are available to download below.",
